<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 5:13PM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Strong Wind Gusts Continue Across Cameron County...
Southerly wind gusts to 40-45 mph are expected to diminish, but
remain possible, into sunset across inland Cameron County, with
sustained winds falling to 25 mph or less. A cold front with
strong northwesterly winds is expected into tonight and an
additional Special Weather Statement or Wind Advisory may be
issued for those winds and wind gusts.</description>
